sentences: Seda filmi ei tasu vaadata, halearmas jama.
Tööl oli täna õpilastega igavene jama.
context: The word 'jama' is an Estonian noun that can refer to several things: 1) Nonsense, trivial or senseless talk, foolishness; 2) Fuss, trouble, confusion. It's often used in expressions like 'ära aja jama suust välja' (don't talk nonsense from your mouth), indicating something is meaningless or not worth paying attention to.
